Note: Beside TensorFlow itself, you'll need to also pass its dependancies on the linker commandline, i.e.,
      '-ltensorflow_cc -ltensorflow_framework -lstdc++ -lm -ldl -lpthread' on Linux and
      '-ltensorflow_cc -ltensorflow_framework -lstdc++ -framework CoreFoundation' on macOS

      For some TensorFlow features (e.g. OpRegistry), it might be necessary to convince the linker to include the whole framework, i.e.,
      '-Wl,--whole-archive -ltensorflow_framework -Wl,--no-whole-archive -ltensorflow_cc -lstdc++ -lm -ldl -lpthread' on Linux and
      '-Wl,-force_load,path/to/libtensorflow_framework.a -ltensorflow_cc -lstdc++ -framework CoreFoundation -framework Security' on macOS
